header.gameNote: SUN BELT TOURNAMENT AT LOUISIANA MONROE

article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 83, Denver 67
article.story: MONROE, La. (AP) -- Tony Hooper scored 26 points and had four steals as Louisiana-Monroe soundly defeated Denver 83-67 in the first round of the Sun Belt Conference Tournament on Wednesday. Louisiana-Monroe, the fourth seed, advanced to the tournament's quarterfinals with the win and on Sunday will play No. 5 seed North Texas. Hooper's 9-of-15 shooting from the floor, including 5-of-9 3-pointers, marked his third consecutive 20-point outing. Jordan Payne added 17 points for the Warhawks, while Gerard Jackson had 12 and Afam Nweke finished with 11. Joseph Jackson led Denver with 16 points while Antonio Porch added 12. Adam Tanner and Nate Rohnert each had 10. Louisiana-Monroe led at the half, 42-34, and opened the second period with a 7-2 run to keep the Pioneers off balance. The Warhawks kept the pressure on Denver and held them without a field goal for a four minute span, while forcing a pair of turnovers. Denver scored its first points in nearly six minutes with a three from Tanner, then Payne hit his first three of the night to push the Warhawks lead to 11 points, 64-53, with less than nine minutes to go. After Hooper stole a Denver pass for his third, breakaway dunk, the momentum swung to Louisiana-Monroe, which had its biggest lead of the night, 78-59. Louisiana-Monroe held the ball for most of the game's final three minutes, holding the Pioneers to four points en route to the win.
